{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ayz41KLVmf1HKnfGWhoJFh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# AI Agent Instructions\n     2→\n     3→## Brainstorming\n     4→\n     5→When the user says \"let's brainstorm on X\", \"brainstorm X\", or similar, immediately\n     6→create `sandbox/brainstorm-{subject}.md` before the discussion begins. Write design\n     7→decisions to that file in real time as the discussion unfolds — do not discuss first\n     8→and reconstruct afterward. The file is the record; chat is ephemeral.\n     9→\n    10→---\n    11→\n    12→<!-- task-management-start -->\n    13→## Task Management\n    14→\n    15→All work in this repository is tracked through a structured task management\n    16→system. Before starting any work, check the task system to understand current\n    17→priorities and status.\n    18→\n    19→**Full documentation:** [`project/tasks/README.md`](project/tasks/README.md)\n    20→\n    21→### Task Types\n    22→\n    23→There are three task types. Every task README has a `Task-type` field.\n    24→\n    25→**USER-TASK** — top-level, human/Oracle-owned. All top-level work must be a\n    26→user-task. No Parent field, no pipeline sections. Created with `new-user-task.sh`.\n    27→\n    28→**USER-SUBTASK** — human/Oracle-owned subtask. Planning steps, reviews,\n    29→approvals, research. Does not go to the pipeline. Can contain further\n    30→user-subtasks or pipeline-subtasks. Created with `new-user-subtask.sh`.\n    31→\n    32→**PIPELINE-SUBTASK** — the pipeline's unit of work. A `build-N` entry point\n    33→authored by the Oracle and submitted to the orchestrator, or a pipeline-internal\n    34→node (component, integrate, test) created by the TM. Pipeline-owned once\n    35→submitted. Can only contain pipeline-subtasks. Created with `new-pipeline-subtask.sh`.\n    36→\n    37→**Hierarchy rules:**\n    38→- All top-level work must be a user-task\n    39→- user-task → user-subtasks and/or pipeline-subtasks\n    40→- user-subtask → user-subtasks and/or pipeline-subtasks\n    41→- pipeline-subtask → pipeline-subtasks only\n    42→- No human-owned node may appear under a pipeline-owned node\n    43→\n    44→**Naming convention:**\n    45→- Top-level tasks: `{6-char-hex-id}-{name}` (e.g. `a3f2c1-my-task`)\n    46→- Subtasks: `{parent-short-id}-{NNNN}-{name}` (e.g. `a3f2c1-0001-design-review`)\n    47→\n    48→The `NNNN` four-digit number **defines the implementation order** of subtasks within\n    49→a parent task. Subtasks must be worked in ascending `NNNN` order unless explicitly\n    50→noted otherwise. The number is assigned at creation time by `Next-subtask-id` in\n    51→the parent's metadata and incremented automatically by the creation scripts.\n    52→\n    53→If the intended implementation order changes after creation, use\n    54→`project/tasks/scripts/reorder-subtasks.py` to renumber the directories to match\n    55→the new order. Never implement subtasks out of their numbered sequence without\n    56→first reordering them — the numbers are the contract.\n    57→\n    58→When a subtask is completed, its directory is renamed with an `X-` prefix\n    59→(e.g. `X-a3f2c1-0001-design-review`). The `X-` prefix marks the subtask as done\n    60→and preserves its number for audit purposes. Completed subtasks are shown with\n    61→`[x]` in the parent README's subtask list.\n    62→\n    63→**Domain ownership:**\n    64→- **Frontend AI** (Oracle/human assistant): creates user-tasks, user-subtasks,\n    65→  and `build-N` pipeline-subtasks. Does NOT edit pipeline-internal subtasks\n    66→  once a build is submitted.\n    67→- **Orchestrator / TM**: operates on pipeline-subtasks and their internal\n    68→  children. Fills in Components, Design, AC. Creates component subtasks.\n    69→  Does NOT touch user-task or user-subtask READMEs.\n    70→\n    71→### Workflow Rules\n    72→\n    73→**Before beginning any task or subtask:** describe its purpose and list all\n    74→subtasks in order. If the task manager is human, wait for their approval\n    75→before starting any implementation work.\n    76→\n    77→**When picking up work:** pull from `backlog/` in top-to-bottom order.\n    78→**When starting a task:** move it to `in-progress/` using `move-task.sh`.\n    79→**When done:** run `complete-task.sh` — no `--parent` for top-level tasks,\n    80→add `--parent` for subtasks.\n    81→\n    82→> **Rule:** Always use the scripts to manage tasks. Never manually edit task\n    83→> `README.md` files to add or remove subtasks, and never manually move task\n    84→> directories between status folders.\n    85→\n    86→> **Rule:** Never create task directories or write task README files directly\n    87→> using shell commands (`cat`, `mkdir`, heredocs, etc.). Always use the\n    88→> provided scripts. Use `Edit` or `Write` only to fill in content sections\n    89→> (Goal, Context, Notes) after a script has created the file.\n    90→\n    91→> **Rule:** When a subtask is finished, always run `complete-task.sh --parent`\n    92→> to mark it `[x]` before moving on to the next subtask.\n    93→\n    94→> **Rule:** Subtask `Status` is binary — only `—` (not done) or `complete`\n    95→> (done). Subtasks do not have statuses like `draft`, `backlog`, or\n    96→> `in-progress`; those apply only to top-level tasks.\n    97→\n    98→### Scripts\n    99→\n   100→Run from the repo root:\n   101→\n   102→```bash\n   103→project/tasks/scripts/new-user-task.sh        --epic main --folder draft --name <task>\n   104→project/tasks/scripts/new-user-subtask.sh     --epic main --folder <status> --parent <task> --name <subtask>\n   105→project/tasks/scripts/new-pipeline-subtask.sh --epic main --folder <status> --parent <task> --name <subtask>\n   106→project/tasks/scripts/move-task.sh            --epic main --name <task> --from <status> --to <status>\n   107→project/tasks/scripts/complete-task.sh        --epic main --folder <status> --name <task>\n   108→project/tasks/scripts/complete-task.sh        --epic main --folder <status> --parent <task> --name <subtask>\n   109→project/tasks/scripts/show-task.sh            --epic main --folder <status> --name <task>\n   110→project/tasks/scripts/delete-task.sh          --epic main --folder <status> --name <task>\n   111→project/tasks/scripts/restore-task.sh         --epic main --folder <status> --name <task>\n   112→project/tasks/scripts/list-tasks.sh           --epic main [--folder <status>] [--depth <n>] [--all] [--tag <tag>]\n   113→```\n   114→<!-- task-management-end -->\n   115→\n   116→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e11f5e49-6198-45d4-a5ae-4a61216498cb","uuid":"db13392c-1c8d-4a54-bf66-92b395b064dd","timestamp":"2026-03-26T04:16:47.236Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/sandbox/user-service-target/CLAUDE.md","content":"# AI Agent Instructions\n\n## Brainstorming\n\nWhen the user says \"let's brainstorm on X\", \"brainstorm X\", or similar, immediately\ncreate `sandbox/brainstorm-{subject}.md` before the discussion begins. Write design\ndecisions to that file in real time as the discussion unfolds — do not discuss first\nand reconstruct afterward. The file is the record; chat is ephemeral.\n\n---\n\n<!-- task-management-start -->\n## Task Management\n\nAll work in this repository is tracked through a structured task management\nsystem. Before starting any work, check the task system to understand current\npriorities and status.\n\n**Full documentation:** [`project/tasks/README.md`](project/tasks/README.md)\n\n### Task Types\n\nThere are three task types. Every task README has a `Task-type` field.\n\n**USER-TASK** — top-level, human/Oracle-owned. All top-level work must be a\nuser-task. No Parent field, no pipeline sections. Created with `new-user-task.sh`.\n\n**USER-SUBTASK** — human/Oracle-owned subtask. Planning steps, reviews,\napprovals, research. Does not go to the pipeline. Can contain further\nuser-subtasks or pipeline-subtasks. Created with `new-user-subtask.sh`.\n\n**PIPELINE-SUBTASK** — the pipeline's unit of work. A `build-N` entry point\nauthored by the Oracle and submitted to the orchestrator, or a pipeline-internal\nnode (component, integrate, test) created by the TM. Pipeline-owned once\nsubmitted. Can only contain pipeline-subtasks. Created with `new-pipeline-subtask.sh`.\n\n**Hierarchy rules:**\n- All top-level work must be a user-task\n- user-task → user-subtasks and/or pipeline-subtasks\n- user-subtask → user-subtasks and/or pipeline-subtasks\n- pipeline-subtask → pipeline-subtasks only\n- No human-owned node may appear under a pipeline-owned node\n\n**Naming convention:**\n- Top-level tasks: `{6-char-hex-id}-{name}` (e.g. `a3f2c1-my-task`)\n- Subtasks: `{parent-short-id}-{NNNN}-{name}` (e.g. `a3f2c1-0001-design-review`)\n\nThe `NNNN` four-digit number **defines the implementation order** of subtasks within\na parent task. Subtasks must be worked in ascending `NNNN` order unless explicitly\nnoted otherwise. The number is assigned at creation time by `Next-subtask-id` in\nthe parent's metadata and incremented automatically by the creation scripts.\n\nIf the intended implementation order changes after creation, use\n`project/tasks/scripts/reorder-subtasks.py` to renumber the directories to match\nthe new order. Never implement subtasks out of their numbered sequence without\nfirst reordering them — the numbers are the contract.\n\nWhen a subtask is completed, its directory is renamed with an `X-` prefix\n(e.g. `X-a3f2c1-0001-design-review`). The `X-` prefix marks the subtask as done\nand preserves its number for audit purposes. Completed subtasks are shown with\n`[x]` in the parent README's subtask list.\n\n**Domain ownership:**\n- **Frontend AI** (Oracle/human assistant): creates user-tasks, user-subtasks,\n  and `build-N` pipeline-subtasks. Does NOT edit pipeline-internal subtasks\n  once a build is submitted.\n- **Orchestrator / TM**: operates on pipeline-subtasks and their internal\n  children. Fills in Components, Design, AC. Creates component subtasks.\n  Does NOT touch user-task or user-subtask READMEs.\n\n### Workflow Rules\n\n**Before beginning any task or subtask:** describe its purpose and list all\nsubtasks in order. If the task manager is human, wait for their approval\nbefore starting any implementation work.\n\n**When picking up work:** pull from `backlog/` in top-to-bottom order.\n**When starting a task:** move it to `in-progress/` using `move-task.sh`.\n**When done:** run `complete-task.sh` — no `--parent` for top-level tasks,\nadd `--parent` for subtasks.\n\n> **Rule:** Always use the scripts to manage tasks. Never manually edit task\n> `README.md` files to add or remove subtasks, and never manually move task\n> directories between status folders.\n\n> **Rule:** Never create task directories or write task README files directly\n> using shell commands (`cat`, `mkdir`, heredocs, etc.). Always use the\n> provided scripts. Use `Edit` or `Write` only to fill in content sections\n> (Goal, Context, Notes) after a script has created the file.\n\n> **Rule:** When a subtask is finished, always run `complete-task.sh --parent`\n> to mark it `[x]` before moving on to the next subtask.\n\n> **Rule:** Subtask `Status` is binary — only `—` (not done) or `complete`\n> (done). Subtasks do not have statuses like `draft`, `backlog`, or\n> `in-progress`; those apply only to top-level tasks.\n\n### Scripts\n\nRun from the repo root:\n\n```bash\nproject/tasks/scripts/new-user-task.sh        --epic main --folder draft --name <task>\nproject/tasks/scripts/new-user-subtask.sh     --epic main --folder <status> --parent <task> --name <subtask>\nproject/tasks/scripts/new-pipeline-subtask.sh --epic main --folder <status> --parent <task> --name <subtask>\nproject/tasks/scripts/move-task.sh            --epic main --name <task> --from <status> --to <status>\nproject/tasks/scripts/complete-task.sh        --epic main --folder <status> --name <task>\nproject/tasks/scripts/complete-task.sh        --epic main --folder <status> --parent <task> --name <subtask>\nproject/tasks/scripts/show-task.sh            --epic main --folder <status> --name <task>\nproject/tasks/scripts/delete-task.sh          --epic main --folder <status> --name <task>\nproject/tasks/scripts/restore-task.sh         --epic main --folder <status> --name <task>\nproject/tasks/scripts/list-tasks.sh           --epic main [--folder <status>] [--depth <n>] [--all] [--tag <tag>]\n```\n<!-- task-management-end -->\n\n","numLines":116,"startLine":1,"totalLines":116}}}
